    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of small, gray Australian parrot. It has a yellow head, red ear patches, and a heavy beak used to crack nuts. The species is bred as a pet globally, with several established color mutations.</Note_Text>
